description.narrative: Improved availability and quality of data on nutrition in UNICEF., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved availability of high quality data on the situation of children and women especially for the SDGs and in humanitarian situations, including through analytic tools and products for programme planning and monitoring, and advocacy.

description.narrative: Good progress for global databases on key nutrition indicators (119 done, 61 public) was made; methodological development to measure emerging issues/ gap areas (SDG 2.2.1, 2.2.2; unhealthy eating and food environment; school-age, adolescent and maternal nutrition, innovation); analytical work and global reports (JME, GNR, SOFI published, on track for; nutrition report and other releases); country support to improve nutrition data and information systems (continued RO/CO support, planning inception meeting for 7 mil/5 country EU grant); and leading nutrition data for children (TEAM secretariat).;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/03/2022
